A multibillion-dollar program to buy electric vehicles for the U.S. Postal Service is far behind its original schedule, plagued by manufacturing mishaps and supplier infighting that threaten a cornerstone of outgoing President Joe Bidenâ€™s fight against climate change. The Postal Service is slated to purchase 60,000 â€œNext Generation Delivery Vehicles,â€ or NGDVs â€” mostly electric â€” from defense contractor Oshkosh, which has a long history of producing military and heavy industrial vehicles, but not postal trucks. Congress provided $3 billion for the nearly $10 billion project in the 2022 Inflation Reduction Act, one of Bidenâ€™s chief legislative accomplishments. But as of November, the Postal Service had received only 93 of the Oshkosh trucks, the agency told The Washington Post â€” far fewer than the 3,000 expected by now. Significant manufacturing difficulties that were not disclosed to the Postal Service for more than a year have stymied production, according to internal company records and four people with knowledge of the events, speaking on the condition of anonymity to avoid professional reprisals. voice_to_text: the thing that's really got me baffled here is why do we know so much more about Luigi than we do about Thomas the math is not mathin here think about it Thomas a twenty year old kid somehow found a way to elude the Secret Service which from what I've been told is the highest level security you could possibly get managed to get a rifle on top of a building extremely close to a former president and fire multiple shots and one of them we were also told actually hit the former president and it feels like that whole thing really just kinda came in with when it comes to Luigi we know about his family history we have a manifesto we have everything talking about why he did it how he created his own weapon we know where he went to school what he studied friends and acquaintances of his have been coming out and talking about them explicitly I see Luigi everywhere right now and I don't think he's going away anytime soon he's kinda spark something amongst people that I think is going to be a topic of conversation for a long time it feels like with Thomas that just went away as fast as they possibly could like they just they wanted to totally erase that whole thing from our memories
